\chessboard
\begin{center}
\fenboard{rnbqkbnr/pppppp0/0000000/8888888/8888888/8888888/8888888/8888888}
\end{center}

\end{document}
```

In this code, we first load the `chessboard` package using the `\usepackage` command. Then, we use the `\chessboard` command to start drawing the board. The FEN notation is passed as an argument to the `\fenboard` command.

Next, we use the `\begin{center}` and `\end{center}` commands to center the board on the page. Finally, the FEN notation for the desired chessboard state is enclosed in `{}`, and the resulting board is displayed using the `\end{center}` command.

Note that you can customize the appearance of the chessboard by using additional options in the `\chessboard` command. For example, you can add a checkerboard pattern using the `boardstyle` option, or add labels for the squares using the `labelstyle` option. See the `chessboard` package documentation for more information on these and other available options.

